<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-05-12T13:23:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-05-12T13:23:00-05:00" n="290" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d290">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">612.119/2859: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at Nogales</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dyer</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Nogales</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-05-12T11:00:00-07:23"><hi rend="italic">May 12,
                                        1920—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 2:57
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Government of Sonora through Presidents Municipal Figueroa of Nogales,
                            Sonora has made application on form which I am forwarding today for
                            permission to export from United States 10,000 rifles and pistols and
                            2,000,000 cartridges, Remington or Winchester, specifications to be
                            supplied later. If not contrary to policy of Department I urge favorable
                            action, notification by wire.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dyer</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>